[2] Global - GPEI 8 Mar 2018
Date: Thu 8 Mar 2018
Source: Global Polio Eradication Initiative [edited]
http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/this-week/


Poliovirus Weekly Update 7 Mar 2018, World Health Organization
--------------------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus cases reported this week: 0
Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2018: 3
Total number of wild poliovirus cases in 2017: 22

New cVDPV cases reported this week: 1 (onset in 2017)
Total number of cVDPV cases in 2018: 0
Total number of cVDPV cases in 2017: 96

Headlines
Summary of newly-reported viruses this week:
- Afghanistan: 1 new wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) positive environmental sample has been reported in Nangarhar province.
- Pakistan: 2 new WPV1 positive environmental samples have been reported, 1 collected in Sindh province, and 1 in Punjab province.
- Democratic Republic of the Congo: 1 case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) reported, from Tanganyika province.

Afghanistan
- No new cases of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) were reported in the past week.
- The total number of officially reported WPV1 cases in Afghanistan in 2018 remains 3.
- The most recent case (by date of onset) was reported in Spinboldak district, Kandahar province, with onset on [6 Jan 2018].
- 1 new WPV1 positive environmental sample was reported this week in Jalalabad district, Nangarhar province, collected on [28 Jan 2018].
- The next set of supplementary immunization days are planned for [12 Mar 2018], during which vaccinators will aim to vaccinate children across 34 provinces using bivalent oral polio vaccine (bOPV). The days are synchronised with a campaign that will take place in Pakistan, part of efforts to interrupt transmission of the virus across the shared border.

Pakistan
- No new cases of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) were reported in the past week.
- The total number of officially reported WPV1 cases in Pakistan in 2017 remains 8. There are no cases reported in 2018.
- The most recent case (by date of onset) was reported in Zhob district, Balochistan province, with onset on [15 Nov 2017].
- 2 new WPV1 positive environmental samples were reported this week. One was collected in Sukkur district, Sindh province, on [8 Feb 2018], and 1 was collected in Dera Ghazi Khan district, Punjab province, on [12 Feb 2018].
- The next set of supplementary immunization days are planned for [12 Mar 2018], during which vaccinators will aim to vaccinate children across 6 provinces using bivalent oral polio vaccine (bOPV). The days are synchronised with a campaign that will take place in Afghanistan, part of efforts to interrupt transmission of the virus across the shared border.

Nigeria
- No new cases of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) were reported in the past week.
- The total number of WPV1 cases for 2016 is 4 and no cases have been reported in 2017 or 2018.
- The most recent case (by date of onset) was reported in Monguno Local Government Area, Borno, with onset on [21 Aug 2016].
- Nigeria continues to implement an emergency response to the detected WPV1 strain and circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) strains affecting the country (last detected in 2016).
- Immunization days went ahead last week, synchronized with campaigns in countries across the Lake Chad basin.
- As part of the emergency response, subnational surveillance continues to be strengthened.

Lake Chad Basin
- The detection of wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) (Borno state, Nigeria in 2016) and circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) (Borno and Sokoto states in 2016) continue to pose a risk to the neighbouring countries of the Lake Chad basin.
- Emergency outbreak response efforts continue across the Lake Chad basin, together with activities to fill subnational surveillance gaps across the region.
- These activities include efforts to vaccinate children at markets, in internally displaced persons camps, and at international borders.
- Immunization days went ahead last week in nearly all countries of the Lake Chad basin.

Central Africa
- 1 new case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. The case was reported in Ankoro district, Tanganyika province, with onset of paralysis on [22 Dec 2017].
- The total number of officially reported cVDPV2 cases in the DRC in 2017 is now 22. There are no cases reported in 2018.
- In response to recent cases, the government of the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) recently announced the cVDPV2 outbreak ongoing in the country a Public Health Emergency of National Concern .
- The Ministry of Health, supported by WHO and partners of the Global Polio Eradication Initiative, remains fully committed to outbreak response, including use of monovalent oral polio vaccine type 2 (mOPV2) across the country, in line with internationally-agreed outbreak response protocols.
- Children living in the districts where the latest cases were reported were last targeted with mOPV2 during December [2017] vaccination days. The next campaign will take place following the completion of microplanning exercises to ensure high vaccination coverage during campaigns.
- Surveillance and immunization activities continue to be strengthened in neighbouring countries.

Horn of Africa
- Circulation of vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) is confirmed in Somalia.
- 3 vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2s (VDPV2s) were isolated from 2 environmental samples collected in Hamarweyn district, Banadir province (Mogadishu), 1 on [4 Jan 2018], and 1 on [11 Jan 2018]. These latest isolates are genetically linked to previously isolated VDPV2s from 2017, collected on [22 Oct 2017] and [2 Nov 2017] from environmental samples collected from Waberi district, Banadir province. In total, 4 environmental samples (with 7 unique virus sequences) positive for cVDPV2 have been collected in Somalia between October 2017, and January 2018.
- No cases of acute flaccid paralysis (AFP) associated with this cVDPV2 have been detected at this time - the viruses were all isolated from environmental samples.
- Surveillance for AFP cases in the area is being strengthened.
- Since detection of the initial isolates in 2017, outbreak response campaigns in line with internationally-agreed guidelines have been implemented, consisting of 2 large-scale immunization activities. A 3rd activity is planned for March 2018.
- WHO and its partners are continuing to support local public health authorities in conducting field investigations and risk assessments to more clearly assess any potential risk of circulation of the identified cVDPV2, and to continue to support the outbreak response and strengthening of disease surveillance.

Middle East
- No new cases of circulating vaccine derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported this week.
- The total number of officially reported cVDPV2 cases in Syria in 2017 remains 74.
- The most recent case (by date of onset) was reported in Boukamal district, with onset on [21 Sep 2017].
- Efforts continue to maintain sensitive surveillance for polioviruses in Syria and neighbouring countries.

Officially reported wild poliovirus cases as of 6 Mar 2018
Total global cases in 2018: 3 (compared with 3 for the same period in 2017)
- Total in endemic countries in 2018: 3 (compared with 3 for the same period in 2017)
- Total in non-endemic countries in 2018: 0 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2017)

- Afghanistan: 3 cases in 2018 (compared with 2 for the same period in 2017), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 6 Jan 18
- Pakistan: 0 case in 2018 (compared with 1 for the same period in 2017), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 15 Nov 17
- Nigeria: 0 case in 2018 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2017), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Aug 16

Total global cases in 2017: 22
- Total in endemic countries: 22
- Total in non-endemic countries: 0

Officially reported cVDPV cases as of 6 Mar 2018
Total global cases in 2018: 0 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2017)
- Syrian Arab Republic: 0 case in 2018 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2017), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 21 Sep 17
- Democratic Republic of the Congo: 0 case in 2018 (compared with 0 for the same period in 2017), onset of paralysis of most recent case: 25 Nov 17

Total global cases in 2017: 96
- Total in endemic countries: 0
- Total in non-endemic countries: 96

