[The above reports contain good news and not so good news.

The good news is that there have been no new cases of either WPV or cVDPV reported in 2018 since the last reports. Another piece of good news is that there has been environmental sampling ongoing in Somalia, a non-endemic country for polio.

The not so good news is that there is continued evidence of poliovirus circulation both WPV and cVDPV as seen in results of environmental sampling. Pakistan and Afghanistan continue to identify WPV in environmental samples in the absence of identifying clinical polio cases, and Somalia has identified cVDPV2 in environmental samples both in 2017 and in 2018, suggesting these viruses have been circulating there for the past 6 months without identified clinical cases of polio. What is unclear is whether the absence of identification of clinical cases associated with the cVDPV2 in Somalia is related to absence of cases, or deficiencies in acute flaccid paralysis (AFP) surveillance. According to data maintained by WHO/EMRO on AFP surveillance, for the years 2017 and 2018, Somalia has a reported non-polio AFP rate of 5-6/100 000 population, a rate consistent with good surveillance (data are downloadable from http://www.emro.who.int/polio/countries/somalia.html). That being said, the continued circulation of the cVDPVs are of concern with respect to the goals of the polio eradication effort, as circulation of a pathogenic poliovirus may lead to clinical cases of polio if susceptible individuals are infected with this virus.

Other not so good news is the identification of another case of cVDPV2 associated polio in the Democratic Republic of the Congo with date of onset 22 Dec 2017, suggesting there has been continued circulation of the cVDPV2 in the Ankoro district, of Tanganyika province.

A map showing the locations of all confirmed cases of polio (both WPV as well as cVDPV associated): http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/.

HealthMap/ProMED maps of areas with identified poliovirus circulation in the above reports are available at:
Somalia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5684227,125
Tanganyika, Democratic Republic of the Congo: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5684227,60107
Pakistan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5684227,140
Afghanistan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5684227,137
- Mod.MPP]
